sp.p:
Hark you, sir—you are an impertinent little rascal—and I've a great mind to horsewhip you;
       but as you are only a boy, and don't know how to behave yourself, I'll forgive you. There!
        (gives money) there's something to buy a riband for your sweetheart.

Thank you, sir; (touching her hat) I am sure I didn't intend to be impudent;
       but when you talked about being afraid, I thought you wouldn't think me a man if I didn't
       resent it:
